parameters.value:
WELCOME

Welcome to the fifth week of the Pulmonary Rehabilitation (PR) Online Maintenance Programme.

This programme is designed for people who have previously taken part in PR and are trying to keep active and keep themselves well. This is the fifth week of a six week programme.

This week's programme consists of the following:

  • Safety Notice
  • Day 1 of Programme
    • An exercise video that includes a warm up, aerobic exercise and a cool down
    • An educational video to watch
  • My Data

SAFETY NOTICE

To ensure your safety during exercise please read the key points below:

  1. WHEN EXERCISING: it is essential that you complete a warm up before exercise and a cool down on finishing.
  2. DO NOT EXERCISE IF:
    • you are having a flare up of your symptoms or you are taking antibiotics or steroids (prednisolone)
    • You do not feel able to exercise for any other medical reason. Seek help from a healthcare professional before attempting exercise.
  3. STOP EXERCISING IF: you get any sudden symptoms such as:
    • Chest pain or tightness
    • Dizziness or Nausea
    • Feeling clammy or cold
    • Feeling increasingly wheezy
    • New or worsening joint pain.
    • Palpitations (a very fast or irregular heart beat)
    • Unusually tired
  4. BEFORE STARTING EXERCISE TODAY make sure you:
    • Have your inhaler in the room with you and you used it as needed (if you have an inhaler)
    • Wear loose, comfortable clothing and supportive non-slip shoes
    • Ensure there is enough space around you to complete the exercises
    • Drink plenty of water so you don't get dehydrated
    • Wait for at least an hour after eating before starting to exercise
More info: NHS UK

By continuing with this programme and clicking on the videos below you agree that you have read and understood the above points and will follow this guidance. You agree that you are exercising at your risk.
